cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on image filtering tasks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests that it could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The tasks of depth map upsampling, saliency map upsampling, texture removal, and semantic segmentation further support the classification under cs.CV. The mention of efficient implementation and fast version of the proposed method suggests that it could also be categorized under graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
